ENTRY            F0659   20251223   20260305   20260305       F105
SUBENT        F0659001   20251223   20260305   20260305       F105
BIB                 10         18
TITLE      Investigation of the Mg-24(alpha,gamma)Si-28 reaction
           and of some Al-27(p,gamma)Si-28 resonances
AUTHOR     (P.J.M.Smulders,P.M.Endt)
INSTITUTE  (2NEDUTR)
REFERENCE  (J,PHY,28,1093,1962)
FACILITY   (VDG,2NEDUTR) The current, varying between 3 and
           8 microA, was largest at the higher energies.
DETECTOR   (NAICR) NaI scintillation crystals were 10 cm long and
           10 cm in diameter.
METHOD     (GSPEC)
MONITOR    (6-C-13(A,N)8-O-16,,DA)
MONIT-REF  (,R.M.Williamson+,J,PR,117,1325,1960)
HISTORY    (20040604C)
           (20120410A) REACTION code in Sub 002,007 was changed,
           COMMON in Sub 002,007 was added. Sample description in
           Sub 002-004 was corrected.
           (20251223A) SD: Corrections in all Subents. Subent 005
           deleted (out of EXFOR scope).
ENDBIB              18
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           21
SUBENT        F0659002   20251223   20260305   20260305       F105
BIB                  6         22
REACTION   (12-MG-24(A,G)14-SI-28,PAR,DA,,REL)
           Number of counts
INC-SOURCE Singly charged helium ions.
SAMPLE     Targets have been used of natural magnesium, and of
           enriched Mg-24, both evaporated onto copper backings.
           Three different targets were used for different alpha
           energy ranges. For E < 3.1 MeV an enriched Mg-24
           target of 15 ug/cm2 was used; for E > 3.1 MeV the
           target was natural Mg of 5 ug/cm2 thickness; in the
           energy range of approximately from 2.7 MeV to 2.93 MeV
           a natural Mg target of about 3 ug/cm2 thickness was
           used.
DETECTOR   (NAICR) NaI scintillation crystal, 10 cm long and
           10 cm in iameter. It was placed as close to the target
           as possible.
           Alpha particle energy was determined with 90 degrees
           deflecting magnet, in which the orbit radius amounted
           to 31 cm. The magnetic field was measured with a Li-7
           magnetic resonance fluxmeter.
           400-channel pulse analyser was used.
STATUS     (CURVE,,P.J.M.Smulders+,J,PHY,28,1093,1962) Fig.2
HISTORY    (20251223U) SD: BIB updated.
ENDBIB              22
