SUBENT        F0659004   20251223   20260305   20260305       F105
BIB                 11         33
REACTION   (12-MG-24(A,G)14-SI-28,PAR,DA,,REL)
            No information about units.
INC-SOURCE Singly charged helium ions.
SAMPLE     Targets have been used of natural magnesium, and of
           enriched Mg-24, both evaporated onto copper backings.
           Three different targets were used for different alpha
           energy ranges. For E < 3.1 MeV an enriched Mg-24
           target of 15 ug/cm2 was used; for E > 3.1 MeV the
           target was natural Mg of 5 ug/cm2 thickness; in the
           energy range of approximately from 2.7 MeV to 2.93 MeV
           a natural Mg target of about 3 ug/cm2 thickness was
           used.
DETECTOR   Alpha particle energy was determined with 90 degrees
           deflecting magnet, in which the orbit radius amounted
           to 31 cm. The magnetic field was measured with a Li-7
           magnetic resonance fluxmeter.
           (NAICR) Two NaI crystals were used to detect gamma
           radiation.
ANALYSIS   Normalization from least-squares analysis. Background
           has been subtracted.
MONITOR    (14-SI-30(P,G)15-P-31,,DA) Any excentricity of the
           target spot with respect to the center of the counter
           turntable was corrected by calibrating on isotropic
           622 keV resonance.
FLAG       (1.) Distance between target and front of
                crystal D=10cm
           (2.) Distance between target and front of
                crystal D=5 cm
MISC-COL   (MISC) Initial abscissa data are given in COS**2.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) No information about source of uncertainty
STATUS     (CURVE,,P.J.M.Smulders+,J,PHY,28,1093,1962)
           Figs 5,6(a,b,c), 7(a,b), 8(a,b), 9(a), 10(a,b)
HISTORY    (20251223U) SD: BIB updated.
ENDBIB              33
